29/11/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Krasimir Kostov, the deputy foreign minister in charge of EU relations, submitted his resignation Friday (November 27th), after he was revealed to have collaborated with the communist-era secret services. 
The commission in charge of opening secret service files announced on Wednesday that three members of the current government were either agents or collaborators with the communist-era service. 
The other two are Minister without Portfolio in charge of Bulgarians abroad Bozhidar Dimitrov and Deputy Interior Minister Pavlin Dimitrov. 
(Darik, Dnevnik, Investor, Mediapool - 27/11/09)
